### Test plan

Workflow (`workflow_test.go`):
- Runner: parse `runner: {name: opus}` and `runner: {command: "make test"}`; both-set → error; KnownFields rejects unknown key in runner.
- Runner 3-state (defect #5): absent → `Stage.Runner==nil`, valid; present-null `runner:` → present, Validate errors (empty); present-empty `runner: {}` → present, Validate errors.
- Gate: parse full gate (checks+seats+pass_threshold+max_rounds+abstraction); parse `tier:` variant; seats+tier both → error; empty gate (no checks/seats/tier) → error; pass_threshold 0 and 1.5 → error; max_rounds 0 → error; check `{name,command}` both → error; KnownFields rejects unknown in gate and in a check.
- Gate 3-state: absent → nil valid; `gate:` (null) → present, Validate errors; `gate: {}` → present, Validate errors.
- default_runner: parse/validate/3-state.
- AC#3 arbitrary stage names (no phase hardcoding): a workflow named e.g. `research → fact-check → draft → tone-police` with runner+gate parses and validates clean.
- Effective-default accessors return 1.0 / 3 when unset.
- Existing `goldenDefaultYAML` + `TestParseYAMLRoundTripsDefault` remain green (Default unchanged).

Registry (`registry_test.go`):
- Parse seats (all fields incl. model_fallbacks), tiers (incl. optional name/use), quorum.
- Validate: tier seat ref to undefined seat → error; tier empty seats → error; seat missing invoke/provider/harness → error; quorum "majority" ok, "bogus" → error, empty → EffectiveQuorum "unanimous"; KnownFields top/seat/tier; trailing-document rejection.
- Golden bytes test for `Default().YAML()` (deterministic, verified) + `ParseYAML(Default().YAML())` round-trip equality.

